cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "overleaf-sync-now: stop AI coding agents from overwriting Overleaf web edits with a stale local Dropbox copy"
version: "0.4.0"
date-released: "2026-05-30"
authors:
  - family-names: Han
    given-names: Lu
    website: "https://luhan.io/"
abstract: >
  A command-line tool and AI-agent skill that keeps a local Dropbox-mirrored
  Overleaf project in sync with the web side, on demand, before every AI
  edit. Probes Overleaf's per-project version history
  (GET /project/{id}/updates) and downloads the project zip
  (GET /project/{id}/download/zip) only when a web-origin change has
  actually occurred, then writes only the files whose contents differ.
  AI coding agents (Claude Code, OpenAI Codex CLI) always edit the latest
  version of a LaTeX paper instead of a stale local copy lagging 10–20
  minutes behind Overleaf's polling-based sync. Includes a PreToolUse hook
  for Claude Code, a Playwright-managed browser login flow that works
  around Chrome 130+ App-Bound Encryption, a recent-mtime guard that
  prevents clobbering in-progress local saves, and sandbox-block detection
  for restricted shells (Codex CLI, CI runners).
keywords:
  - overleaf
  - latex
  - dropbox
  - sync
  - claude-code
  - codex
  - ai-tools
  - agent-skill
